default3.8
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOfcom is legally obliged to ensure an affordable postal service and can reintroduce regulation on any Universal Service product. Ofcom concluded in March 2013 that Royal Mail’s servi
defaultces were affordable to consumers and small and medium sized businesses.
default Ofcom said (in their report on the affordability of postal services, published 19 March 2013):
default&#xa0;
default“The evidence we have collected indicates that universal postal services are affordable 
defaultfor both residential consumers (including low income and other vulnerable consumers) and businesses (including small and medium businesses) at current prices. We have reviewed the price changes that are due to take effect from 2 April 2013 (as announced by
default Royal Mail in March 2013), and consider that universal postal services will continue to be affordable following these changes.”
